  "prompt": "How do I prevent iMovie for iPad from cropping the top and bottom off my video that was originally taken in portrait orientation?",
  "response": "To prevent iMovie from cropping your portrait-oriented video on iPad, try these steps:\n\n1. When you first import the video, tap on the video in the timeline.\n\n2. Look for the \"Crop\" or \"Fit\" option (usually represented by an aspect ratio icon).\n\n3. Choose \"Fit\" instead of \"Fill\" or \"Crop\" to preserve the entire video frame.\n\n4. If the option isn't immediately visible, tap the video and look for cropping/scaling controls.\n\nIf these steps don't work, you can also:\n- Rotate the video before importing\n- Use a different video editing app that handles portrait video better\n- Edit the video on a computer with more flexible editing options\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these suggestions?",
